Daisy the baby giraffe has not had the easiest start in life.

The ‘leggy brunette’ was abandoned by her mother, and so has to be fed through a tube which is being kept in place by a bandage around her long neck.

Orphan Daisy was born an unusually large baby giraffe, so her mother did not see her as a calf and therefore stopped producing milk when she was born.

