Without the valuable nutrients from her mother’s milk, Daisy's white blood cell count became dangerously low and she contracted an infection.

This led to the staff at the School of Veterinary Medicine at Tufts University in Grafton, Massachusetts to place a bandage on Daisy's neck so she could be fed intravenously.

Visitors will be able to catch a glimpse of Daisy when the zoo opens again on 12 April 2014.

